data.sentence: Tengo que confesar que a veces no me gusta tu forma de ser.
data.translation: I have to confess that sometimes I don't like your way of being.

data.sentence: Luego te me desapareces y no entiendo muy bien por qué.
data.translation: Then you disappear on me and I don't understand very well why.

data.sentence: No dices nada romántico cuando llega el atardecer.
data.translation: You don't say anything romantic when sunset arrives.

data.sentence: Te pones de un humor extraño con cada luna llena al mes.
data.translation: You get in a strange mood with each full moon of the month.

data.sentence: Pero a todo lo demás le gana lo bueno que me das.
data.translation: But everything else is won by the good that you give me.

data.sentence: Solo tenerte cerca siento que vuelvo a empezar.
data.translation: Just having you near, I feel that I'm starting over.

data.sentence: Yo te quiero con limón y sal.
data.translation: I want you with lemon and salt.

data.sentence: Yo te quiero tal y como estás.
data.translation: I want you just as you are.

data.sentence: No hace falta cambiarte nada.
data.translation: It's not necessary to change anything.

data.sentence: Yo te quiero si vienes o si vas.
data.translation: I want you if you come or if you go.

data.sentence: Si subes, si bajas, si no estás seguro de lo que sientes.
data.translation: If you go up, if you go down, if you're not sure what you feel.

data.sentence: Tengo que confesarte ahora nunca creí en la felicidad.
data.translation: I have to confess to you, I never believed in happiness.

data.sentence: A veces, algo se le parece pero es pura casualidad.
data.translation: Sometimes, something seems like it, but it's pure coincidence.

data.sentence: Luego me vengo a encontrar con tus ojos, me dan algo más.
data.translation: Then I come to find your eyes, they give me something more.
